        "name": "Doesn't the Bible say to give to the poor and help those in need?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, Scripture calls us to help. But helping isn't the same as enabling. Real help addresses the root cause, not just the symptom. Proverbs 19:17 calls us to have mercy on the poor-and mercy means showing kindness that actually improves someone's situation, not creating a cycle of dependency. James 2:15-16 points out that just telling someone to 'stay warm and well fed' without addressing why they're cold or hungry isn't help at all. The best help teaches someone to provide for themselves, builds their dignity, and points them toward God as their source-not toward you."
        }
