          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Ask yourself: Does this help them become more independent or more dependent on me? If you're giving a handout, teach them a skill instead. If you're solving their problem, guide them through solving it themselves. If you're praying for them, teach them to pray. If you're making decisions for them, help them learn to decide. Real help requires more time and effort than just rescuing someone-but it's the only help that actually works. And remember Galatians 6:5: each person should carry their own load. Your job is to strengthen them to carry it, not to carry it for them."
